# Generating Sprites

Use the local `@tot/spritegen` CLI to produce consistent, transparent, game-ready
sprites. Do NOT hand-author sprites or invent image files.

## Always delegate to a background subagent

Generation blocks for ~1-3 minutes (and costs OpenAI credits). NEVER run it on the
main thread. Instead launch a background subagent and keep working:

- Use the Task tool with `subagent_type: shell` and `run_in_background: true`.
- Give it the exact command below, and tell it to report back the parsed `--json`
  result: `ok`, `chosen.verdict.score`, `outputs`, and the `wiring` block.
- When it completes you'll be notified; then do the wiring on the main thread.

## Command

```bash
# Item icon:
pnpm --filter @tot/spritegen gen generate \
  --preset item-icon --subject "<concrete visual description>" \
  --id <snake_case_item_id> --n 3 --json

# World entity (256x256; scaffolds an EntityDefinition with --wire):
pnpm --filter @tot/spritegen gen generate \
  --preset entity --subject "<concrete visual description>" \
  --id <snake_case_entity_id> --display-name "<Name>" --kind <kind> \
  --tags <tag1,tag2> --n 3 --json
```

- `--id` must match (or become) the id in `items.ts` / `entities.ts`.
- `--subject` is a concrete art description, not the display name.
- Use `--n 3` (best-of-N) and parse `--json`. Add `--vision-qa` for a stricter check.
- `--display-name`/`--kind`/`--tags` only shape the scaffolded entity (default kind `prop`).
- Only `item-icon` and `entity` presets exist today.

## Acting on the result

If `ok: true`, the chosen candidate beat QA (`chosen.verdict.score`). If `ok: false`,
inspect `error`/`rejects` and retry with a refined `--subject`. Outputs land in
`AvailableAssets/` with a 1024 master in `tools/spritegen/out/masters/`.

## Wiring it into the game

The `wiring` block gives the exact lines. Pass `--wire` to auto-edit, or do it by hand:

- Items: add the `import` + `TEXTURE_MANIFEST` entry to `apps/client/src/assets/manifest.ts`,
  then set `worldTextureId` on the matching definition in `packages/shared/src/content/items.ts`.
- Entities: `--wire` adds the manifest entry AND scaffolds a minimal `EntityDefinition`
  into `packages/shared/src/content/entities.ts` (added to `ENTITY_DEFINITIONS`, so it
  appears in both the Level and Entity editors). Refine its gameplay fields afterward.

Then bump the PATCH in `apps/client/src/version.ts` (registering art is a client change).

## Setup

Requires `tools/spritegen/.env` with `OPENAI_API_KEY` (gitignored). See `tools/spritegen/README.md`.
